					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-5986717#post-4153944</guid>
				<title>Curious about introduced plants...</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-5986717/scp-3779#post-4153944</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Fri, 15 Feb 2019 00:56:24 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>Robert Gresham</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>1827929</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>The file states that introduced plants will behave like the ones already within SCP-3779. Does that mean they will also mimic foreign materials that are introduced later? And the decay rate is faster than normal plants of that type.</p> <p>Example: a radish is brought in. Later a researcher forgets a plastic pen cap in overnight. Does the radish become plastic and when later removed remain plastic, but it decays as a radish does at an accelerated rate?</p> <p>Sorry if this is clearer to other readers.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-5986717#post-3818136</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-5986717/scp-3779#post-3818136</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Wed, 30 May 2018 16:57:29 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>ATL4Sv2</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>4163950</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>I have no idea why, but I think this one is just flat out cool. It's reminiscent of other anomalous properties of other SCP's, but it has its own <em>twist</em> that I can't really explain. I'd love to see someone make a rendition of the flower-human hybrids. Great work.</p> <p>+1</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-5986717#post-3810224</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-5986717/scp-3779#post-3810224</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Wed, 23 May 2018 14:42:16 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>TL333s</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>1304786</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>There's not much going on here, but it's kind of cute? Like, I really appreciate that the plants are so dedicated to their mimicry that they'll start looking like corpses after killing a dude.</p> <p>I'll say though that footnote 3 doesn't add anything, that much is obvious from the info given in footnote 2.</p> 
				 	]]>
